fields.prompt: Is there board and founding team buy-in for the CD process?
Who is the business visionary?
Who is the business execution?
Who is the product visionary?
Who is the product execution?
What is your mission statement? This should be around 2 paragraphs describing your vision for the product, business, and market.
What are the 3 to 5 core values the founding team believes in?
What problem are you solving? What is the general goal of the product?
What intellectual property of ours will be unique? What will be patented or considered a trade secret?
Who are the day-to-day users of the product?
What is the biggest pain your customer has?
Which products do your customers already use?
What are the features of your product? (no more than 10!)
How will users initially buy from you? Through a direct salesperson, a rep or distributor, a partner, a retail store, mail order, on the web?
How much do similar existing products cost?
How many copies could you sell to each customer?
How will users hear about you? Advertising, word of mouth, seminars, partners...?
Which market type do we think we’re in?
What is the total cost of ownership of your product, including training, deployment, and additional personnel/tech infrastructure?
Have you checked to see if anyone else has important IP in our space?
Who are the influencers and recommenders?
Is the pain the same on all levels of the company? If not, how does it vary?
How would your product change their daily lives? How about their lives?
What is the customer benefit of each feature?
Upload a distribution channel diagram
How much do customers spend to build custom solutions to the problem?
How many total units could you sell at $1 each?
How much funding will we need for 2-3 passes around discovery & validation?
Upload a simplified architectural diagram
What IP of other's will we need to license, infringe on, or work around?
Whose budget will pay for it?
If your customers could wave a magic wand and change anything, what would it be?
Summarize a day in the life of your customers
How much will the channel cost in direct expenses & channel discounts
If in a new market, how much money does our product save the customer in time, money, expenses
How many at $1,000,000 each? What is the maximum price at which a unit would sell?
Is there enough funding for 2-3 passes?
Is there is an existing budget or will one need to be approved?
What do people do today to solve their problem without your product?
What is the smallest feature set they would pay for?
What are the indirect costs? Presales support, channel promo dollars, etc.
Will we be changing the rules/models of pricing or following suit? If offering new pricing models, what are they?
At what price would half of potential customers say "yes"?
How long will we stay in discovery and validation?
Who are the decision makers?
Where on the problem recognition scale is each type of customer? (latent need, active need, or visionary)
Which others pieces & products are required for a customer to use or buy our product? How do they get those pieces?
What is your preliminary sales price?
Would it be easier to sell if it were packaged differently? Sold in separate modules that each cost less? Combined with other products? Built into a full solution?
Who else needs to approve the purchase?
What is the organizational impact of this pain -- individual, departmental, corporate? Personal, household?
How many units will you sell in the first 12 and 24 months?
Where will you find your visionary first paying customers? In what role, type of company and industry segment?
Is this a mission-critical, have-to-have product or a luxury nice-to-have?
